data.text:
Louis Boisson was a French politician born on January 15, 1908, in Saint-Laurent-la-Vernède, Gard. He spent his life serving in various political roles until his passing on February 12, 1991, in Le Tréport, Seine-Maritime. His contributions to French politics reflect the dynamics of his time, and he is remembered for his involvement in the political landscape during the mid-20th century.
